In Uganda, road traffic accidents pose a significant challenge, with a high number of fatalities reported on a weekly basis. The Uganda police issues a weekly crime report that includes data on road crashes. However, these reports often lack the necessary details to fully understand the nature and severity of the accidents. This blog aims to use publicly available unstructured data from newspaper articles to get a nuanced picture of what, when, and critical aspects of road accidents to identify hot-spots for targeted actions to enhance road safety.






